name: TWIST-testing
description: TWIST is a dynamic year-to-year supply-demand model including consumer and producer stocks to estimate global export prices of crops.

parameters.name: crop
parameters.description: Choose your crop of interest for which you want to know the price dynamics. You can choose from wheat, rice or corn.

parameters.name: inclusion_of_production_decline
parameters.description: If the scenario should include production reduction comparable with a) production decline in breadbasket areas (top 10 producers for the corresponding crop) in 2007/08 AND b) locust upsurge in East Africa 2020, this parameter should be set to "True". If not, this parameter should be set to "False".

parameters.name: length_of_scenario
parameters.description: Number of years for which the price dynamics for the corresponding crop is projected from 2020.

parameters.name: inclusion_of_export_restriction
parameters.description:
In 2007/08 some regions restrict the export of harvested products.
Export restricting nations for wheat: Argentina, Bolivia, Ethiopia, India, Kazakhstan, Nepal, Pakistan, Serbia, Syria, Ukraine, Guinea.
Export restricting nations for rice: Argentina, Bangladesh, Brazil, Cambodia, China, Ecuador, Egypt, Ethiopia, India, Indonesia, Madagascar, Myanmar, Nepal, Pakistan, Tanzania, Thailand, Vietnam, Guinea.
Export restricting nations for corn: China, Ethiopia, Guinea, India, Kenya, Nepal, Serbia, Ukraine, Zambia.

If the scenario should consider this export restrictions, it should be set to "2007_2008". 

Besides export bans, Argentina and Russia implemented higher export taxes for corn and wheat, respectively. The following export reduction is once assumed to be 25% and once assumed to be 50% for the corresponding country.
If the scenario with corn should include the 25%-effective export tax from Argentina, this parameter should be set to "2007_2008_ARG25".  If the scenario with corn should include the 50%-effective export tax from Argentina, this parameter should be set to "2007_2008_ARG50". If the scenario with wheat should include, this 25%-effective export tax from Russia the parameter should be set to "2007_2008_RUS25". If the scenario with wheat should include the 50%-effective export tax from Russia, this parameter should be set to "2007_2008_RUS50". 

If the scenario should include no export restriction, this parameter should be set to "none". 

Here is a short list of possible parameters depending on the crop.
Wheat: "2007_2008", "2007_2008_RUS25", "2007_2008_RUS50" or "none".
Corn: "2007_2008", "2007_2008_ARG25", "2007_2008_ARG50" or "none".
Rice: "2007_2008" or "none"

outputs.name: WM_price_scenario [US$/mt]
outputs.description: the world market price in us$ per mega ton of corresponding crop for the particular year under the chosen parameters (and therefore scenario).
outputs.unit_description: us-dollar per mega ton of crop

outputs.name: WM_price_baseline [US$/mt]
outputs.description: the world market price in us$ per mega ton of the baseline for the particular year. this value shall be used to compare it with the world market price for the chosen scenario.
outputs.unit_description: us-dollar per mega ton of crop

outputs.name: Ending_stock_scenario [mt]
outputs.description: the global stock is the aggregation of producers' and consumers'  stocks for the corresponding crop and is given after the harvest. the global stock is given in units of mega ton, for the particular year and under the chosen parameters (and therefore scenario).

outputs.name: Ending_stock_baseline [mt]
outputs.description: the global stock is the aggregation of producers' and consumers'  stocks for the corresponding crop and is given after the harvest. the global stock for the baseline is given in units of mega ton and for the particular year. this value shall be used to compare it with the global stock for the chosen scenario.

outputs.name: Production_baseline [mt]
outputs.description: global production of corresponding crop in units of mega ton for the particular year of the baseline. this value shall be used to compare it with the global production for the chosen scenario.

outputs.name: Consumption+baseline [mt]
outputs.description: global consumption of corresponding crop in units of mega ton for the particular year for the baseline. this value shall be used to compare it with the global consumption for the chosen scenario.

outputs.name: Production_scenario [mt]
outputs.description: global production of corresponding crop in units of mega ton for the particular year under the chosen parameters (and therefore scenario).

outputs.name: Consumption_scenario [mt]
outputs.description: global consumption of corresponding crop in units of mega ton for the particular year under the chosen parameters (and therefore scenario).
